#  Cluster Analysis_
#  RQ2SUM1~SUM5

#####  #####
#####  #####
#####  #####
# install.packages("readxl")
# install.packages("cluster")
# install.packages("factoextra")
# install.packages("ggplot2")

library(readxl)
## Warning: package 'readxl' was built under R version 4.4.2
library(cluster)
library(factoextra)
## Warning: package 'factoextra' was built under R version 4.4.3
## Loading required package: ggplot2
## Warning: package 'ggplot2' was built under R version 4.4.2
## Welcome! Want to learn more? See two factoextra-related books at https://goo.gl/ve3WBa
library(ggplot2)

##### Step 0&1 #####
# 
file_path <- "Scores_5Factors(6Items).xlsx"

#  Excel 
data <- read_excel(file_path)
cat("\n")
## 
##### Step 2 #####
# SUM1, SUM2, SUM3, SUM4, SUM5
target_vars <- c("SUM1", "SUM2", "SUM3", "SUM4", "SUM5")
data.sub <- data[, target_vars]

# 
if (any(is.na(data.sub))) {
    cat("...\n")
    data.sub <- na.omit(data.sub)
}

#  (Standardization)
#  (Z-score)
data.sub.centered <- scale(data.sub, center = TRUE, scale = TRUE)

##### Step 3 (Determine Optimal Clusters) #####
#  (Elbow Method)   (Silhouette Method)

# (1)  WSS (Within Sum of Squares) - 
p1 <- fviz_nbclust(data.sub.centered, kmeans, method = "wss") +
    ggtitle("Elbow Method (WSS)") +
    geom_vline(xintercept = 3, linetype = 2) #  3

# (2)  (Average Silhouette)
p2 <- fviz_nbclust(data.sub.centered, kmeans, method = "silhouette") +
    ggtitle("Average Silhouette")

# 
print(p1)

print(p2)

##### Step 4 K-means  #####
#  k
#  k=3 Step 3 
set.seed(123) # 
k_num <- 3

KM.res <- kmeans(
    x = data.sub.centered, # 
    centers = k_num, # 
    nstart = 25, #  ( 25  50 )
    iter.max = 100 # 
)

##### Step 5 #####
# (1)  data  "cluster" 
# 
data$cluster <- factor(KM.res$cluster, labels = paste0("Cluster", 1:k_num))

# (2) 
cat("\n#####  #####\n")
## 
## #####  #####
cluster_prop <- table(data$cluster) / length(data$cluster)
print(round(cluster_prop, 4))
## 
## Cluster1 Cluster2 Cluster3 
##   0.3726   0.3782   0.2492
# (3)  ()
#  ()
cat("\n#####  () #####\n")
## 
## #####  () #####
cluster_means <- aggregate(data[, target_vars],
    by = list(cluster = data$cluster), FUN = mean
)
print(cluster_means)
##    cluster     SUM1     SUM2     SUM3     SUM4     SUM5
## 1 Cluster1 17.83656 20.48817 15.02366 13.49677 17.39785
## 2 Cluster2 26.84322 31.38771 25.50000 23.22669 21.95127
## 3 Cluster3 36.54019 37.59486 35.58521 35.32797 32.01929
# (4)  z-score  ()
cat("\n#####  (Standardized Centers) #####\n")
## 
## #####  (Standardized Centers) #####
print(round(KM.res$centers, 3))
##     SUM1   SUM2   SUM3   SUM4   SUM5
## 1 -0.812 -0.918 -0.880 -0.863 -0.605
## 2  0.095  0.275  0.135  0.058 -0.092
## 3  1.071  0.954  1.111  1.203  1.043
# (5) 
p_cluster <- fviz_cluster(KM.res,
    data = data.sub.centered,
    palette = "jco",
    ggtheme = theme_minimal(),
    main = paste0("Cluster Analysis Results (k=", k_num, ")")
)
print(p_cluster)

#  (Optional)
ggsave("Cluster_Analysis_Result.png", plot = p_cluster, width = 10, height = 8)
